(467, 'China', 'Crime Risk', 'internationalsos', '2021-05-17', 'Not Recieved', '\nInbound business travellers\n‚Ä¢ Essential travel to Taiwan may be possible subject to an itinerary- and profile-specific\nreview This assessment is made jointly by our medical and security professionals.\n‚Ä¢ For further information, advice and current restrictions, see the International SOS\nLocation Guides andmedical alertsand the COVID-19 information within thePandemic\nInformation Site, including Travel Restrictions Flight Operations and Screening.\nIn-country workforce\n‚Ä¢ Closely follow all official directives and abide by them. Monitor reliable sources for\ninformation relating to changes to directives.\n‚Ä¢ Understand your company‚Äôs medical and security triggers for changes to in-\ncountry posture.\nHealth advice\n‚Ä¢ Obtain profile-specific advice prior to any travel, taking into account the extent to which\nyour age and health may make you more vulnerable to the COVID-19 virus.\n‚Ä¢ Do not travel if you are sick; people who are sick face the risk of being tested and\nquarantined. Monitor your health and seek medical attention if you develop flu-like\nsymptoms, following the local procedure for your location.\n‚Ä¢ Pay strict attention to hygiene. Wash your hands frequently and carry hand sanitiser\nfor use when soap and water are not readily available. Wear a mask whenever\nrequired to. Even if not required, consider wearing a mask if you have to go out in\npublic.\n‚Ä¢ Avoid crowded places. In public areas, as much as possible, keep 1-2 metres (3-6 feet)\naway from others.\n', '\nTaiwan (China): COVID-19: Continue to defer non-essential\ntravel amid further stringent entry restrictions from 19 May\n', '1', '3', '', 'ty Alert -International SOS<riskinsights@internationalsos.com>\nSent on:Monday, May 17,20219:26:50 PM\nTo: Akash.Tomar@gds.ey.com\nSubject:1traveller now -Advisory: Taiwan (China) -COVID-19: Continue to defer non-essential travel amid\nfurther stringent entry restrictions from 19May\n', NULL),
