(503, 'France', 'Crime Risk', 'internationalsos', '2021-05-11', 'Not Recieved', '\n‚Ä¢ Follow all official directives, including any evacuation orders. Stay away from areas\nalong the Alaknanda river if conducting journeys to or through Devprayag in the\ncoming hours . Contact the state disaster operations centre at 1070 or +91-\n9557444486 for further information.\n‚Ä¢ Reconfirm the status of routes, including National Highway (NH)- 7 via Devprayag,\nbefore setting out. Allow additional time to complete journeys.\n‚Ä¢ Do not attempt to drive through flooded areas. If you come across a flooded road, turn\naround and find another route to your destination.\n‚Ä¢ Expect disruption to essential services, including electricity supply, in areas affected by\nthe severe weather conditions. Charge all communication devices and, where feasible,\nkeep extra batteries for backup.\n‚Ä¢ Monitor our alerts on India for further updates.\n', '\nIndia: Uttarakhand state: Plan journeys accounting for\ndisruption in coming days due to heavy rain, flash flooding\n', '2', '3', '', ' -Advisory: India -Uttarakhand state: Plan journeys accounting fordisruption in\ncoming days due to heavy rain, flash flooding\n', NULL),
(504, 'Iraq', 'Crime Risk', 'internationalsos', '2021-05-14', 'Not Recieved', '\nInbound business travellers\n‚Ä¢ Essential travel to Iraq may be possible subject to an itinerary- and profile-specific\nreview. This assessment is made jointly by our medical and security professionals.\n‚Ä¢ For further information, advice and current restrictions, see the International SOS\nLocation Guides andmedical alerts, and the COVID-19 information within thePandemic\nInformation Site, includingTravel Restrictions, Flight Operations and Screening.\nIn-country people\n‚Ä¢ Closely follow all official directives and abide by them. Monitor reliable sources for\ninformation relating to changes to directives.\n‚Ä¢ Understand your organisation‚Äôs medical and security triggers for changes to in-country\nposture.\nHealth advice\n‚Ä¢ Obtain profile-specific advice prior to any travel, taking into account the extent to which\nyour age and health may make you more vulnerable to the COVID-19 virus.\n‚Ä¢ Do not travel if you are sick. People who are sick risk being tested and quarantined.\nMonitor your health and seek medical attention if you develop flu-like symptoms,\nfollowing the local procedure for your location.\n‚Ä¢ Pay strict attention to hygiene. Wash your hands frequently and carry hand sanitiser for\nuse when soap and water are not readily available. Wear a mask whenever required\nto. Even if not required, consider wearing a mask if you have to go out in public.\n‚Ä¢ Avoid crowded places. In public areas, as much as possible, keep three to six feet (1-2\nmetres) away from others.\n', '\nIraq: COVID-19: Continue to abide by official directives despite\neasing of internal restrictions\n', '2', '3', '', ' -Advisory: Iraq -COVID-19: Continue to abide byofficial directives despite easing\nofinternal restrictions\n', NULL),
