(512, 'France', 'Crime Risk', 'internationalsos', '2021-05-13', 'Not Recieved', '\n‚Ä¢ If in Central, Southern or Tel Aviv district, minimise movement in the coming days and\nabide by all official directives issued by the emergency services and civil authorities.\nEnsure to stay in the vicinity of the nearest shelter or protected space.\n‚Ä¢ Defer all travel to locations within 25 miles (40km) of the border with Gaza until further\nnotice.\n‚Ä¢ Understand the immediate actions to take upon hearing an air raid siren and remain\naware of the location of the nearest shelter or protected space. The length of an air raid\nsiren represents the amount of time one has to enter their secure space. When in a\nsecure space, remain there for at least ten minutes. If another air raid warning is heard\nduring this time, remain inside the secure space for a further ten minutes.\n‚Ä¢ For further information on what to do during a rocket attack, please visit the Israel\nDefense Forces Home Front Command website (access from outside Israel may not\nbe possible) and consult this Preparedness Information document.\n‚Ä¢ The above advice is not exhaustive. Consult our Standing Travel Advice for Israel for\nfull recommendations.\n', '\nIsrael: Minimise non-essential movement in Southern, Central,\nTel Aviv districts following intensification of rocket fire\n', '2', '3', '', ' -Advisory: Israel -Minimise non-essential movement in Southern, Central, Tel Aviv\ndistricts following intensification ofrocket fire\n', NULL),
