(532, 'France', 'Crime Risk', 'internationalsos', '2021-05-10', 'Not Recieved', '\n‚Ä¢ Avoid the vicinity of the USCIS building until the situation normalises. Shelter in place if\nnearby.\n‚Ä¢ Anticipate heightened security in the area and abide by all official directives.\n‚Ä¢ Anticipate road disruption in the vicinity.\n‚Ä¢ Monitor our US alerts for updates.\n', '\nUnited States: Orlando (Florida state): Avoid vicinity of USCIS\nbuilding due to potential shooting; shelter in place if nearby\n', '2', '3', '', ' -Advisory: United States -Orlando (Florida state): Avoid vicinity ofUSCIS\nbuilding due to potential shooting; shelter in place if nearby\n', NULL),
(533, 'France', 'Political War Risk', 'internationalsos', '2021-05-19', 'Not Recieved', '\n‚Ä¢ Avoid the area until the fire is brought under control and roads reopen.\n‚Ä¢ If already in the area, follow official directives and leave when safe to do so.\n‚Ä¢ Monitor our US alerts for updates.\n', '\nUnited States: Pittsburgh (Pennsylvania state): Avoid vicinity of\nGulf Tower due to ongoing fire\n', '2', '3', '', ' -Advisory: United States -Pittsburgh (Pennsylvania state): Avoid vicinity ofGulf\nTower due to ongoing fire\n', NULL),
(534, 'France', 'Crime Risk', 'internationalsos', '2021-05-15', 'Not Recieved', '\n‚Ä¢ Avoid the affected area to minimise inconvenience.\n‚Ä¢ If travel in the area or along nearby routes is unavoidable, allow additional time to\ncomplete journeys due to diverted traffic.\n‚Ä¢ Expect a heightened security presence and abide by all official directives.\n‚Ä¢ Monitor our US alerts for updates.\n', '\nUnited States: San Antonio (Texas state): Avoid Prue Patrol on\n7400 block of John Smith Drive due to ongoing security\noperation, shooting\n', '2', '3', '', ' -Advisory: United States -San Antonio (Texas state): Avoid Prue Patrol on7400\nblock of John Smith Drive due to ongoing security operation, shooting\n', NULL),
(535, 'France', 'Political War Risk', 'internationalsos', '2021-05-09', 'Not Recieved', '\n‚Ä¢ Consult the National Weather Service website for more information on the tornado and\nactive warnings.\n‚Ä¢ If you are in an area covered by a tornado warning, immediately take shelter and stand\nfast. Follow all official directives.\n‚Ä¢ Expect disruption to infrastructure in affected areas. Roads may be blocked by fallen\ntrees or debris. Reconfirm the status of routes before setting out.\n‚Ä¢ Monitor our alerts on the US for further updates.\n', '\nUnited States: Tennessee state: Stand fast, follow official\ndirectives amid passage of tornado near Munford\n', '2', '3', '', ' -Advisory: United States -Tennessee state: Stand fast, follow official directives\namid passage oftornado near Munford\n', NULL),
(536, 'France', 'Crime Risk', 'internationalsos', '2021-05-11', 'Not Recieved', '\n‚Ä¢ Consult the NWS website for more information on weather-related advisories.\n‚Ä¢ Expect possible disruption to infrastructure in affected areas. Roads may be blocked by\nfallen trees or debris; reconfirm the status of routes before setting out.\n‚Ä¢ Monitor our alerts on the US for further updates.\n', '\nUnited States: Texas state: Tornado warning issued for parts of\nHouston, Trinity, Walker counties; exercise caution; stand fast\nin affected areas\n', '2', '3', '', ' -Advisory: United States -Texas state: Tornado warning issued for parts of\nHouston, Trinity, Walker counties; exercise caution; stand fast in affected areas\n', NULL),
(537, 'Armenia', 'Political War Risk', 'internationalsos', '2021-05-07', 'Not Recieved', '\n‚Ä¢ Anticipate disruption in the vicinity of the event and plan journeys accordingly.\n‚Ä¢ If travelling nearby, anticipate a heightened security force presence and allow\nadditional time for journeys.\n‚Ä¢ Liaise with local contacts for information on related gatherings in other locations.\n‚Ä¢ Monitor our Armenia alerts for updates.\n', '\nArmenia: Yerevan: Plan journeys bypassing planned protest at\nFreedom Square on 7 May\n', '2', '1', '', ' -Notice: Armenia -Yerevan: Plan journeys bypassing planned protest at Freedom\nSquare on7May\n', NULL),
(538, 'France', 'Crime Risk', 'internationalsos', '2021-05-10', 'Not Recieved', '\n‚Ä¢ Liaise with local contacts for information on the trial location. Plan routes bypassing it\nand any other areas where related gatherings are taking place.\n‚Ä¢ If travel through an affected location is unavoidable, ensure routes are clear before\nsetting out and leave additional time to complete journeys.\n‚Ä¢ Anticipate a heightened police presence and possible traffic disruption in affected\nareas. Carry relevant identification and travel documents. Follow all official directives.\n‚Ä¢ Monitor our Georgia alerts for updates and refer to our detailed alert on the political\nsituation for more information.\n', '\nGeorgia: Tbilisi: Anticipate, avoid gatherings linked to\nopposition leader‚Äôs court hearing on 10 May\n', '2', '1', '', ' -Notice: Georgia -Tbilisi: Anticipate, avoid gatherings linked to opposition leader‚Äôs\ncourt hearing on10May\n', NULL),
(539, 'France', 'Political War Risk', 'internationalsos', '2021-05-15', 'Not Recieved', '\n‚Ä¢ Liaise with local contacts for the exact details of the protest, as well as any affected\nroutes.\n‚Ä¢ If travelling near the demonstration, reconfirm the status of routes before setting out\nand allow additional time for journeys.\n‚Ä¢ Anticipate heightened security around the gathering and follow all official directives,\nincluding any restrictions linked to COVID-19.\n‚Ä¢ Leave an area at the first sign that protesters and/or the police are gathering. In the\nevent of unrest, and if it is safe to do so, relocate to a secure location such as your\noffice or accommodation. Remain there until the situation stabilises.\n‚Ä¢ Monitor our alerts on Georgia for updates.\n', '\nGeorgia: Tbilisi: Plan routes bypassing anti-government protest\non 16 May\n', '2', '1', '', ' -Notice: Georgia -Tbilisi: Plan routes bypassing anti-government protest on16May\n', NULL),
(540, 'France', 'Crime Risk', 'internationalsos', '2021-05-13', 'Not Recieved', '\n‚Ä¢ Reconfirm any scheduled appointments at government medical colleges and hospitals\nbefore setting out. Make alternative arrangements, where required. Anticipate an\nincreased demand for services at private facilities.\n‚Ä¢ Reconfirm that access to hospital premises is not obstructed during any\ndemonstrations.\n‚Ä¢ Plan journeys bypassing gatherings to minimise localised delays.\n‚Ä¢ Monitor our India alerts for updates.\n', '\nIndia: Gujarat state: Anticipate disruption due to ongoing strike\nby government medical staff\n', '2', '1', '', ' -Notice: India - Gujarat state: Anticipate disruption due to ongoing strike by\ngovernment medical staff\n', NULL),
(541, 'France', 'Political War Risk', 'internationalsos', '2021-05-12', 'Not Recieved', '\n‚Ä¢ Liaise with local contacts to remain apprised of any political gatherings. Avoid them\ndue to the risk of violence.\n‚Ä¢ Leave an area as soon as political activists or the police begin to gather.\n‚Ä¢ Refrain from engaging in public discussions on sensitive topics such as politics.\n‚Ä¢ Anticipate heightened security around gatherings and follow all official directives.\n‚Ä¢ Monitor our India alerts for updates.\n', '\nIndia: West Bengal: Anticipate intermittent politically motivated\nviolence; avoid related protests\n', '2', '1', '', ' -Notice: India - West Bengal: Anticipate intermittent politically motivated violence;\navoid related protests\n', NULL),
(542, 'France', 'Crime Risk', 'internationalsos', '2021-05-17', 'Not Recieved', '\n‚Ä¢ Avoid all protests as a precaution and to minimise delays. Liaise with local contacts to\nremain apprised of demonstrations in your location.\n‚Ä¢ Reconfirm the status of routes before setting out and allow additional time for journeys.\n‚Ä¢ Expect heightened security and associated disruption near protests. Comply with all\nofficial directives and carry relevant identification documents to ease passage through\nany security checks.\n‚Ä¢ Leave an area at the first sign of unrest or if a crowd is forming. Move to a secure\nlocation, such as your accommodation or office. Remain there until the situation has\nstabilised.\n‚Ä¢ Monitor our alerts on Indonesia for updates.\n', '\nIndonesia: Urban centres: Anticipate, avoid pro-Palestinian\ndemonstrations on 18 May\n', '2', '1', '', ' -Notice: Indonesia - Urban centres: Anticipate, avoid pro-Palestinian demonstrations\non18May\n', NULL),
(543, 'France', 'Political War Risk', 'internationalsos', '2021-05-15', 'Not Recieved', '\n‚Ä¢ Liaise with your security provider regarding the feasibility of movement during the\nprotests. Avoid all gatherings due to the credible potential for unrest.\n‚Ä¢ Anticipate a heightened security presence around gatherings. Comply with all\ndirectives issued by the security forces and carry relevant identification documents to\nease passage through checkpoints.\n‚Ä¢ The above advice is not exhaustive. Contact your nearest Assistance Centre for\nprofile- and itinerary-specific information.\n‚Ä¢ Monitor our alerts on Iraq for updates.\n', '\nIraq: Liaise with dedicated security provider regarding\nfeasibility of movement during nationwide pro-Palestinian\ndemonstrations on 15 May\n', '2', '1', '', ' -Notice: Iraq -Liaise with dedicated security provider regarding feasibility of\nmovement during nationwide pro-Palestinian demonstrations on15May\n', NULL),
(544, 'France', 'Crime Risk', 'internationalsos', '2021-05-13', 'Not Recieved', '\n‚Ä¢ We do not hold specific flight schedules. Reconfirm flights with the airport or\nrelevant airline. In the event of cancellations, your travel agent will be able to assist\nwith alternative arrangements.\n‚Ä¢ Monitor our Israel alerts for updates.\n', '\nIsrael: Reconfirm flights as Ben Gurion International Airport\nreopens for outbound routes\n', '2', '1', '', ' -Notice: Israel -Reconfirm flights as Ben Gurion International Airport reopens for\noutbound routes\n', NULL),
(545, 'France', 'Political War Risk', 'internationalsos', '2021-05-17', 'Not Recieved', '\n‚Ä¢ Liaise with local contacts to ascertain the locations of related rallies and exercise\ncaution around protest flashpoints. In Israel, these include the cities of Haifa, Umm al-\nFahm (both Haifa district), Lod, Ramle (both Central district) and Nazareth (Northern\ndistrict). In the West Bank, demonstrations are likely at checkpoints and key road\njunctions, as well as in main urban centres.\n‚Ä¢ Avoid all related demonstrations due to the potential for unrest. The security forces are\nliable to use tear gas and/or rubber bullets at short notice to disperse crowds.\n‚Ä¢ Monitor our alerts for related updates.\n', '\nIsrael, Palestinian Territories: Exercise caution at protest\nflashpoints, anticipate disruption on 18 May during planned\ngeneral strike\n', '2', '1', '', ' -Notice: Israel, Palestinian Territories -Exercise caution at protest flashpoints,\nanticipate disruption on18May during planned general strike\n', NULL),
(546, 'France', 'Crime Risk', 'internationalsos', '2021-05-18', 'Not Recieved', '\n‚Ä¢ Liaise with local contacts to ascertain the locations of related rallies and exercise\ncaution around protest flashpoints. In Israel, these include the cities of Jerusalem,\nHaifa, Umm al-Fahm (both Haifa district), Lod, Ramle (both Central district) and\nNazareth (Northern district). In the West Bank, demonstrations are likely at checkpoints\nand key road junctions, as well as in main urban centres.\n‚Ä¢ Avoid all related demonstrations due to the potential for unrest. The security forces are\nliable to use tear gas and/or rubber bullets at short notice to disperse crowds.\n‚Ä¢ Monitor our alerts for related updates.\nASSISTANCE\n', '\nIsrael, Palestinian Territories: Exercise caution at protest\nflashpoints, anticipate disruption on 18 May during planned\ngeneral strike\n', '2', '1', '', ' -Notice: Israel, Palestinian Territories -Exercise caution at protest flashpoints,\nanticipate disruption on18May during planned general strike\n', NULL),
(547, 'France', 'Political War Risk', 'internationalsos', '2021-05-08', 'Not Recieved', '\n‚Ä¢ Liaise with local contacts to remain apprised of any protests in your area. Avoid all\nsuch events as a precaution and to minimise travel delays.\n‚Ä¢ Leave an area at the first sign of unrest, or if a crowd is forming. Remain in a secure\nlocation, such as your local office or accommodation, until the situation has stabilised.\n‚Ä¢ Abide by all official directives, including COVID-19-related regulations.\n‚Ä¢ Monitor our alerts for updates.\n', '\nIsrael, Palestinian Territories: Expect further protests, unrest\nduring planned \'Day of rage\' on 8 May\n', '2', '1', '', ' -Notice: Israel, Palestinian Territories -Expect further protests, unrest during\nplanned \'Day ofrage\' on8May\n', NULL),
(548, 'France', 'Crime Risk', 'internationalsos', '2021-05-20', 'Not Recieved', '\n‚Ä¢ Reconfirm the status of routes around protest venues before setting out, and allow\nadditional time to complete journeys.\n‚Ä¢ If travelling near demonstrations, anticipate a heightened police presence and follow all\nofficial directives.\n‚Ä¢ Comply with internal COVID-19-related measures.\n‚Ä¢ Monitor our Japan alerts for updates.\n', '\nJapan: Tokyo: Anticipate localised disruption during pro-\nPalestinian march on 21 May\n', '2', '1', '', ' -Notice: Japan - Tokyo: Anticipate localised disruption during pro-Palestinian\nmarch on21May\n', NULL);
