(549, 'France', 'Political War Risk', 'internationalsos', '2021-05-20', 'Not Recieved', '\n‚Ä¢ Where possible, plan journeys bypassing gatherings to minimise delays and allow\nadditional travel time. Reconfirm the status of routes around protest venues before\nsetting out.\n‚Ä¢ If travelling near demonstrations, anticipate a heightened police presence and follow all\nofficial directives.\n‚Ä¢ Comply with internal COVID-19-related measures.\n‚Ä¢ Monitor our Japan alerts for updates.\n', '\nJapan: Tokyo: Expect disruption at Harumi Triton Square during\nweekly anti-Olympics demonstrations from 21 May\n', '2', '1', '', ' -Notice: Japan - Tokyo: Expect disruption at Harumi Triton Square during weekly\nanti-Olympics demonstrations from 21May\n', NULL),
(550, 'France', 'Crime Risk', 'internationalsos', '2021-05-11', 'Not Recieved', '\nInbound business travellers\n‚Ä¢ Essential travel to Maldives may continue subject to an itinerary- and profile- specific\nreview. This assessment is made jointly by our health and security professionals.\n‚Ä¢ Monitor the websites of the Department of Immigration ( IMUGA ) and the Ministry of\nTourismfor information on entry and visa restrictions, as well as quarantine measures.\n‚Ä¢ For further information, advice and current restrictions, see the International SOS\nLocationGuidesandmedicalalertsandtheCOVID-19informationwithinthe Pandemic\nInformation Site, includingTravel Restrictions, Flight Operations and Screening.\nIn-country workforce\n‚Ä¢ Closely follow all official directives and abide by them. Monitor reliable sources for\ninformation relating to changes to directives.\n‚Ä¢ Understand your organisation‚Äôs medical and security triggers for changes to in- country\nposture.\nHealth advice\n‚Ä¢ Obtain profile- specific advice prior to any travel, taking into account the extent to which\nyour age and health may make you more vulnerable to the COVID-19 virus.\n‚Ä¢ Do not travel if you are sick. People who are sick face the risk of being tested and\nquarantined. Monitor your health and seek medical attention if you develop flu- like\nsymptoms, following the local procedure for your location.\n‚Ä¢ Pay strict attention to hygiene. Wash your hands frequently and carry hand sanitiser for\nuse when soap and water are not readily available. Wear a mask whenever required\nto. Even if not required, consider wearing a mask if you have to go out in public.\n‚Ä¢ Avoid crowded places. In public areas, as much as possible, three- to- six feet (1- 2\nmetres) away from others.\n', '\nMaldives: COVID-19: Follow official directives amid ongoing\ncurfew, other restrictions\n', '2', '1', '', ' -Notice: Maldives -COVID-19: Follow official directives amid ongoing curfew,\nother restrictions\n', NULL),
(551, 'France', 'Crime Risk', 'internationalsos', '2021-05-10', 'Not Recieved', '\n‚Ä¢ Normal movement can resume in the area.\n‚Ä¢ Monitor our alerts on Maldives for notable developments.\n', '\nMaldives: Male: Normal movement can resume in vicinity of\nBihuroazu Kamanaa Mosque following conclusion of security\noperation (Revised)\n', '2', '1', '', ' -Notice: Maldives -Male: Normal movement can resume in vicinity ofBihuroazu\nKamanaa Mosque following conclusion ofsecurity operation (Revised)\n', NULL),
(552, 'France', 'Crime Risk', 'internationalsos', '2021-05-11', 'Not Recieved', '\n‚Ä¢ Avoid non-essential journeys to HIGH travel risk states, including Tamaulipas.\nOverland travel to rural areas should be closely co-ordinated with trusted local\ncontacts.\n‚Ä¢ Maintain a heightened level of awareness at all time. All valuables should be concealed\nand business travellers should use a low-profile vehicle.\n‚Ä¢ Carefully plan all aspects of your itinerary and be confident in accommodation,\ntransport, communication and security arrangements prior to travelling. If conducting\nsignificant overland travel, do so during daylight hours only.\n‚Ä¢ Crime poses a significant risk in Mexico and criminals are often armed. If accosted,\navoid doing anything to resist or antagonise the assailant. If you are involved in a\nserious crime, contact your local embassy or consulate, as well as your local support\nnetwork.\n‚Ä¢ Monitor our Mexico alerts for updates.\n', '\nMexico: Tamaulipas state: Exercise caution amid likely crime\nincrease following killing of cartel leader\n', '2', '1', '', ' -Notice: Mexico - Tamaulipas state: Exercise caution amid likely crime increase\nfollowing killing ofcartel leader\n', NULL),
(553, 'France', 'Crime Risk', 'internationalsos', '2021-05-16', 'Not Recieved', '\nInbound business travellers\n‚Ä¢ Essential travel to Pakistan may be possible subject to an itinerary- and profile-specific\nreview. This assessment is made jointly by our medical and security professionals.\n‚Ä¢ For further information, advice and current restrictions, see the International SOS\nLocation Guides and medical alerts and the COVID-19 information within the\nPandemic Information Site, including Travel Restrictions, Flight Operations and\nScreening.\nIn-country people\n‚Ä¢ Closely follow all official directives and abide by them. Monitor reliable sources of\ninformation relating to changes to directives.\n‚Ä¢ Understand your company\'s medical and security triggers for changes to in-country\nposture.\nHealth advice\n‚Ä¢ Obtain profile-specific advice prior to any travel, taking into account the extent to which\nyour age and health may make you more vulnerable to the COVID-19 virus.\n‚Ä¢ Do not travel if you are sick. People who are sick risk being tested and quarantined.\nMonitor your health and seek medical attention if you develop flu-like symptoms,\nfollowing the local procedure for your location.\n‚Ä¢ Pay strict attention to hygiene. Wash your hands frequently and carry hand sanitiser for\nuse when soap and water are not readily available. Wear a mask whenever required\nto. Even if not required, consider wearing a mask if you have to go out in public.\n‚Ä¢ Avoid crowded places. In public areas, as much as possible, keep three to six feet (1-2\nmetres) away from others.\n', '\nPakistan: COVID-19: Abide by official directives following\nextension of restrictions until 30 May\n', '2', '1', '', ' -Notice: Pakistan -COVID-19: Abide byofficial directives following extension of\nrestrictions until 30May\n', NULL),
(554, 'France', 'Crime Risk', 'internationalsos', '2021-05-14', 'Not Recieved', '\n‚Ä¢ Anticipate disruption during the motorcade and plan journeys accordingly.\n‚Ä¢ Local nationals and journalists attending the rally should exercise caution and ensure\naccess to reliable methods of communication in the event of an emergency.\n‚Ä¢ If travelling in the vicinity, anticipate heightened security, follow all official directives and\nallow additional time for journeys.\n‚Ä¢ Monitor our South Africa alerts for updates.\n', '\nSouth Africa: Johannesburg, environs: Anticipate disruption,\nplan journeys accordingly during motorcade protest on 15 May\n', '2', '1', '', ' -Notice: South Africa - Johannesburg, environs: Anticipate disruption, plan journeys\naccordingly during motorcade protest on15May\n', NULL),
