(569, 'France', 'Crime Risk', 'internationalsos', '2021-05-12', 'Not Recieved', '\n‚Ä¢ If in Central, Southern or Tel Aviv district, minimise movement until 13 May and abide\nby all official directives.\n‚Ä¢ Understand the immediate actions to take on hearing air raid warnings and be aware of\nthe location of the nearest air raid shelter. The length of an air raid siren represents the\namount of time one has to enter secure space. When in a secure space, remain there\nfor at least ten minutes. If another air raid warning is heard during this time, remain\ninside the secure space for a further ten minutes.\n‚Ä¢ For further information on what to do during a rocket attack, please visit the Israel\nDefense Forces Home Front Command website (access from outside Israel may not\nbe possible).\n‚Ä¢ As temporary closures of airspace and Ben Gurion International Airport may take\nplace, reconfirm all flight itineraries in the coming days and anticipate residual\ndisruption at the airport after such closures.\n‚Ä¢ Defer all travel to locations within 25 miles (40km) of the border with Gaza until further\nnotice. If you are already in these locations, minimise movement and ensure you stay\nin the vicinity of the nearest air raid shelter.\n‚Ä¢ Monitor our Israel alerts for updates.\n', '\nIsrael: Central, Southern, Tel Aviv districts: Minimise movement\nuntil 13 May amid fresh rocket attacks\n', '2', '5', '', ' -Special Advisory: Israel - Central, Southern, Tel Aviv districts: Minimise\nmovement until 13May amid fresh rocket attacks\n', NULL),
(570, 'France', 'Crime Risk', 'internationalsos', '2021-05-11', 'Not Recieved', '\n‚Ä¢ If in Tel Aviv district, stand fast until the situation normalises.\n‚Ä¢ Understand the immediate actions to take on hearing air raid warnings and remain\naware of the location of the nearest air raid shelter. Understand the immediate actions\nto take on hearing air raid warnings. The length of an air raid siren represents the\namount of time one has to enter their secure space. When in a secure space, remain\nthere for at least ten minutes. If another air raid warning is heard during this time,\nremain inside the secure space for a further ten minutes.\n‚Ä¢ For further information on what to do during a rocket attack, please visit the Israel\nDefense Forces (IDF) Home Front Command website (access from outside Israel may\nnot be possible).\n‚Ä¢ Monitor our Israel alerts for updates.\n', '\nIsrael: Tel Aviv district: Stand fast amid ongoing rocket attack;\naccount for staff\n', '2', '5', '', ' -Special Advisory: Israel - Tel Aviv district: Stand fast amid ongoing rocket attack;\naccount forstaff\n', NULL),
(571, 'France', 'Crime Risk', 'internationalsos', '2021-05-17', 'Not Recieved', '\nIn-country workforce\n‚Ä¢ Continue to defer non-essential travel to affected areas, including Gujarat, as well as\nDadra and Nagar Haveli and Daman and Diu union territories, until 19 May.\n‚Ä¢ We do not hold specific information on flights or other transport. Reconfirm schedules\nwith the relevant service provider before setting out. In the event of cancellations, your\ntravel agent will be able to help with alternative arrangements.\n‚Ä¢ Monitor the IMDwebsite for the latest forecast and be prepared to adjust itineraries at\nshort notice.\nThose in areas forecast to be affected\n‚Ä¢ Minimise movement in the aforementioned areas and follow all official directives. If in\nan affected location, stand fast in or move to a secure accommodation with a\nconfirmed supply of essential commodities such as water, food and electricity.\n‚Ä¢ Stay away from rivers and other water bodies, as well as low-lying coastal areas, which\nare susceptible to storm surges and flooding.\n‚Ä¢ Any essential movement should be undertaken after confirming that intended\ndestinations and routes are unaffected by flooding. Avoid surge-prone or flooded\nareas. Ensure that your vehicle is in good condition and appropriately equipped for the\nweather conditions before setting out.\n‚Ä¢ Disruption to essential services, such as electricity, is likely in worst-affected areas.\nCharge all communications devices and laptops. Ensure you have access to back-up\ncharging options such as power banks.\n‚Ä¢ Prepare a \'grab bag\' with essentials such as a torch, water and high-energy foods, in\ncase an emergency relocation becomes necessary.\n', '\nIndia: Western region: Continue to defer non-essential travel to\nareas most affected by Very Severe Cyclonic Storm Tauktae\n(Revised)\n', '4', '3', '', ' -Advisory: India -Western region: Continue to defer non-essential travel to areas\nmost affected byVery Severe Cyclonic Storm Ta