(597, 'Brazil', 'Crime Risk', 'internationalsos', '2021-05-06', 'Not Recieved', '\n‚Ä¢ Crime is a significant concern in Brazil and criminals are often armed. If targeted, do\nnothing to resist or antagonise the assailant(s).\n‚Ä¢ If you are in the vicinity of a violent incident, quickly move to a secure location as soon\nas it is safe to do so and remain there until the situation normalises.\n‚Ä¢ Plan routes through Rio de Janeiro in advance. Use official taxis or hire a private\nvehicle and driver. Do not self-drive unless you are familiar with local conditions as\nGPS systems may direct travellers through favelas (shanty towns). Public transport is\nnot suitable for travellers.\n‚Ä¢ Consult our city security guide for Rio de Janeiro city for more information on crime.\n‚Ä¢ Monitor our Brazil alerts for updates.\n', '\nBrazil: Rio de Janeiro: Shoot-out during police operation in\nJacarezinho favela highlights incidental risks posed by violent\ncrime\n', '8', '1', '', ' -Notice: Brazil - Rio de Janeiro: Shoot-out during police operation in Jacarezinho\nfavela highlights incidental risks posed byviolent crime\n', NULL),
