(605, 'France', 'Crime Risk', 'internationalsos', '2021-05-11', 'Not Recieved', '\n‚Ä¢ Abide by all official directives, including restrictions on public gatherings and mobility\nlinked to the COVID-19 pandemic.\n‚Ä¢ Be respectful of religious and cultural practices.\n‚Ä¢ Prepare for potential delays in government services. Reconfirm any appointments\nscheduled during the holiday period.\n‚Ä¢ Maintain a low profile, remain vigilant and minimise time spent near potential militant\ntargets, such as religious sites, marketplaces and public transport hubs. Report any\nsuspicious behaviour or suspect packages to the authorities.\n‚Ä¢ This advice is not exhaustive. The nature of observance, cultural sensitivities and travel\ndisruption during Eid al-Fitr differs by country and region. Contact your nearest\nAssistance Centre for country- and profile-specific advice prior to travel.\n', '\nAsia & the Pacific: Anticipate disruption, heightened security\nduring Eid al-Fitr festival; abide by COVID-19-related restrictions\n', '11', '1', '', ' -Notice: Asia & the Pacific -Anticipate disruption, heightened security during Eid\nal-Fitr festival; abide byCOVID-19-related restrictions\n', NULL),
