(612, 'France', 'Crime Risk', 'internationalsos', '2021-05-09', 'Not Recieved', '\n‚Ä¢ Liaise with local contacts for information on related protests in your area. Potential\nflashpoints for further gatherings include university campuses, public squares,\ngovernment buildings, mosques and Palestinian refugee camps.\n‚Ä¢ Foreign nationals should avoid all protests as a precaution. Local nationals and\njournalists attending the protests should exercise caution and ensure access to reliable\ncommunications in the event of an emergency.\n‚Ä¢ If travel in the vicinity of demonstrations is unavoidable, anticipate a heightened\nsecurity force presence, follow all official directives and allow additional time for\njourneys.\n‚Ä¢ Monitor our Jordan alerts for updates.\n', '\nJordan: Urban centres: Anticipate, avoid further demonstrations\nlinked to violence in Jerusalem\n', '12', '1', '', ' -Notice: Jordan -Urban centres: Anticipate, avoid further demonstrations linked to\nviolence in Jerusalem\n', NULL),
(613, 'France', 'Crime Risk', 'internationalsos', '2021-05-20', 'Not Recieved', '\n‚Ä¢ Liaise with local contacts to remain apprised of any ongoing or planned protests in your\narea. Plan routes bypassing all such events as a precaution. If travel near a protest site\nis unavoidable, ensure routes are clear prior to setting out and leave additional time to\ncomplete journeys.\n‚Ä¢ Do not stop to watch or photograph protests. Leave an area at the first sign of unrest or\nif a crowd is forming.\n‚Ä¢ Expect a heightened security presence around protests and follow all official directives.\n‚Ä¢ Anticipate possible disruption to communication networks, including messaging apps,\nand ensure you have access to back-up means of communication.\n‚Ä¢ Monitor our alerts on Kazakhstan for updates.\n', '\nKazakhstan: Urban centres: Plan routes bypassing planned\nopposition protests on 22-23 May\n', '12', '1', '', ' -Notice: Kazakhstan -Urban centres: Plan routes bypassing planned opposition\nprotests on22-23May\n', NULL),
