(648, 'France', 'Crime Risk', 'internationalsos', '2021-05-16', 'Not Recieved', '\nIn-country workforce\n‚Ä¢ Defer non-essential travel to areas expected to be affected in Gujarat and Dadra and\nNagar Haveli and Daman and Diu union territory until 19 May. Such districts are\nAmreli, Devbhoomi Dwarka, Gir Somnath, Jamnagar, Junagarh, Kutch, Morbi,\nPorbandar, Rajkot (all Gujarat) and Diu (Dadra and Nagar Haveli and Daman and Diu).\n‚Ä¢ We do not hold specific information on flights or other transport. Reconfirm\nschedules with the relevant service provider before setting out. In the event of\nschedules with the relevant service provider before setting out. In the event of\ncancellations, your travel agent will be able to help with alternative arrangements.\n‚Ä¢ Monitor the IMDwebsitefor the latest forecast and be prepared to adjust itineraries at\nshort notice.\nThose in areas forecast to be affected\n‚Ä¢ Minimise movement in the aforementioned districts and follow all official directives. If in\nan affected location, stand fast in or move to a secure accommodation with a\nconfirmed supply of essential commodities such as water, food and electricity.\n‚Ä¢ Stay away from rivers and other water bodies, as well as low-lying coastal areas, which\nare susceptible to storm surges and flooding.\n‚Ä¢ Any essential movement should be undertaken after confirming that intended\ndestinations and routes are unaffected by flooding.Avoid surge-prone or flooded areas.\nEnsure that your vehicle is in good condition and appropriately equipped for the\nweather conditions before setting out.\n‚Ä¢ Disruption to essential services, such as electricity, is likely in worst-affected areas.\nCharge all communications devices and laptops. Ensure you have access to back-up\ncharging options such as power banks.\n‚Ä¢ Prepare a \'grab bag\' with essentials such as a torch, water and high-energy foods, in\ncase an emergency relocation becomes necessary.\n', '\nIndia: Southern, western regions: Continue to anticipate\ndisruption during passage of Very Severe Cyclonic Storm\nTauktae (Revised)\n', '17', '3', '', ' -Advisory: India -Southern, western regions: Continue to anticipate disruption\nduring passage ofVery Severe Cyclonic Storm Tauktae (Revised)\n', NULL),
(649, 'India', 'Crime Risk', 'internationalsos', '2021-05-14', 'Not Recieved', '\n‚Ä¢ Monitor the India Meteorological Department (IMD)websitefor information on the\nweather system and related warnings. Be prepared to adjust itineraries at short notice.\n‚Ä¢ We do not hold specific information on flights or other modes of transport.\nReconfirm schedules with the relevant service provider before setting out. In the event\nof cancellations, your travel agent will be able to help with alternative arrangements.\n‚Ä¢ Ascertain the status of roads before setting out and allow additional time for journeys.\nDo not attempt to cross flooded roads. If you come across one, seek an alternative\nroute to your destination.\n‚Ä¢ Anticipate disruption to essential services such as electricity and telecommunications in\naffected areas. Charge all communications devices and laptops. Ensure you have\naccess to back-up charging options such as power banks.\n‚Ä¢ Monitor our India alerts for updates.\n', '\nIndia: Southern, western regions: Continue to anticipate heavy\nrain, disruption during passage of weather system\n', '17', '3', '', ' -Advisory: India -Southern, western regions: Continue to anticipate heavy rain,\ndisruption during passage ofweather system\n', NULL),
(650, 'France', 'Political War Risk', 'internationalsos', '2021-05-15', 'Not Recieved', '\n‚Ä¢ Plan journeys bypassing the protest as a precaution and to minimise travel delays.\n‚Ä¢ Local nationals and journalists attending the rally should exercise caution and ensure\naccess to reliable communications in the event of an emergency.\n‚Ä¢ If travelling in the vicinity, anticipate heightened security, follow all official directives and\nallow additional time for journeys.\n‚Ä¢ Monitor our Jordan alerts for updates.\n', '\nJordan: Karameh (Balqa governorate): Anticipate disruption\nnear border with Israel due to ongoing protest\n', '17', '3', '', ' -Advisory: Jordan -Karameh (Balqa governorate): Anticipate disruption near\nborder with Israel due to ongoing protest\n', NULL),
(651, 'France', 'Crime Risk', 'internationalsos', '2021-05-08', 'Not Recieved', '\n‚Ä¢ Avoid the affected area. If you are nearby, minimise movement until the situation\nstabilises.\n‚Ä¢ If planning to travel to the affected area in the coming hours, ensure routes are clear\nprior to setting out.\n‚Ä¢ Follow all directives issued by emergency officials.\n‚Ä¢ Monitor our US alerts for updates.\n', '\nUnited States: Aventura (Florida state): Avoid vicinity of\nAventura Mall due to ongoing police operation\n', '17', '3', '', ' -Advisory: United States -Aventura (Florida state): Avoid vicinity ofAventura\nMall due to ongoing police operation\n', NULL),
(652, 'India', 'Crime Risk', 'internationalsos', '2021-05-14', 'Not Recieved', '\nInbound business travellers\n‚Ä¢ Defer all travel to India due to restrictions related to COVID-19. This assessment is\nmade jointly by our medical and security professionals.\n‚Ä¢ For further information, advice and current restrictions, see the International SOS\nLocation Guides and medical alerts and the COVID-19 information within the\nPandemic Information Site, including Travel Restrictions Flight Operations and\nScreening.\nIn-country people\n‚Ä¢ Closely follow all official directives and abide by them. Monitor reliable sources for\ninformation relating to changes to directives.\n‚Ä¢ Understand your organisation‚Äôs medical and security triggers for changes to in-country\nposture.\n‚Ä¢ Refer to our regional COVID-19 alert for detailed advice.\nHealth advice\n‚Ä¢ Obtain profile-specific advice prior to any travel, taking into account the extent to which\nyour age and health may make you more vulnerable to the COVID-19 virus.\n‚Ä¢ Do not travel if you are sick; people who are sick face the risk of being tested and\nquarantined. Monitor your health and seek medical attention if you develop flu-like\nsymptoms, following the local procedure for your location.\n‚Ä¢ Pay strict attention to hygiene: Wash your hands frequently and carry hand sanitiser for\nuse when soap and water are not readily available. Wear a mask whenever required\nto. Even if not required, consider wearing a mask if you have to go out in public.\n‚Ä¢ Avoid crowded places. In public areas, as much as possible, keep three-to-six feet (1-2\nmetres) away from others.\n', '\nIndia: COVID-19: Continue to defer travel, abide by state-\nspecific directives (Correction)\n', '17', '1', '', ' -Notice: India - COVID-19: Continue to defer travel, abide bystate-specific\ndirectives (Correction)\n', 'covid-1'),
(653, 'Bangladesh', 'Crime Risk', 'internationalsos', '2021-05-19', 'Not Recieved', '\nManagers\n‚Ä¢ Closely monitor COVID-19-related developments for their impact on staff mobility or\nassociated security risks.\n‚Ä¢ Ensure access to reliable, nuanced information to inform workforce communication and\nbusiness decision-making.\n‚Ä¢ Regularly re-evaluate whether it is best for your international assignees and\ndependants to remain in-country or to relocate. If you decide to relocate them, this\nshould be done as soon as possible.\n‚Ä¢ Consider the circumstances that influence their ability to remain in-country and work\nwith the restrictions, directives and mitigation measures of the authorities. These\ninclude:\no The ability to procure basic goods and services.\no Access to communications.\no Access to quality medical care, the usual standard of local medical care and the\nlocal health system‚Äôs capability to manage a sudden surge in demand.\no The ability and comfort level of international assignees to stay for an extended\nperiod at their destination with limited or no support.\n‚Ä¢ Ensure the strict compliance of your workforce with local government containment\nefforts.\n‚Ä¢ Ensure country-specific Business Continuity Plans are regularly reviewed and focused\non next steps.\nIn-country international assignees\n‚Ä¢ Carefully consider whether it is best for you and your family to remain where you are\nnow or to relocate. Plan accordingly.\n‚Ä¢ Review the circumstances that influence your ability to remain in-country (and work\nwith the restrictions, directives and mitigation measures of the authorities).\n‚Ä¢ Review your personal need to be in an alternative location.\n‚Ä¢ Review your personal need to be in an alternative location.\nIn-country people\n‚Ä¢ Closely follow all official directives and abide by them. Monitor reliable sources for\ninformation relating to changes to directives.\n‚Ä¢ Understand your company‚Äôs medical and security triggers for changes to in-country\nposture.\n‚Ä¢ Defer non-essential domestic travel that would entail long periods of time in close\nproximity to other members of the public.\n‚Ä¢ Ensure you have provisions in place at your accommodation and worksites to support\na stand-fast period of seven days (i.e. food, water, medicine).\nInbound business travellers\n‚Ä¢ Continue to defer all travel to Bangladesh, India and Nepal due to restrictions related to\nCOVID-19. This assessment is made jointly by our medical and security professionals.\n‚Ä¢ Monitor officialwebsites for the latest updates on conditions for entry into Bangladesh,\nIndia and Nepal, as well as related quarantine measures. Avoid rumours and\nmisinformation. Monitor and confirm developments by liaising with the authorities,\nincluding the nearest relevant embassy or consulate.\n‚Ä¢ For further information, advice and current restrictions, see the International SOS\nLocation Guides andmedical alertsand the COVID-19 information within thePandemic\nInformation Site, includingTravel Restrictions, Flight Operations and Screening.\nHealth advice\n‚Ä¢ Obtain profile-specific advice prior to any travel, taking into account the extent to which\nyour age and health may make you more vulnerable to the COVID-19 virus.\n‚Ä¢ Do not travel if you are sick; people who are sick face the risk of being tested and\nquarantined. Monitor your health and seek medical attention if you develop flu-like\nsymptoms, following the local procedure for your location.\n‚Ä¢ Pay strict attention to hygiene: Wash your hands frequently and carry hand sanitiser\nfor use when soap and water are not readily available. Wear a mask whenever\nrequired to. Even if not required, consider wearing a mask if you have to go out in\npublic.\n‚Ä¢ Avoid crowded places. In public areas, as much as possible, keep three-to-six feet (1-2\nmetres) away from others.\n', '\nAsia & the Pacific: South Asia: Continue to defer travel as\nCOVID-19 pandemic, associated consequences persist\n', '18', '3', '', ' -Advisory: Asia & the Pacific - South Asia: Continue to defer travel as COVID-19\npandemic, associated consequences persist\n', NULL),
