(663, 'France', 'Crime Risk', 'internationalsos', '2021-05-18', 'Not Recieved', '\n‚Ä¢ Exercise heightened vigilance during the electoral cycle. Seek expert itinerary- and\nprofile-specific advice prior to travel to Mexico.\n‚Ä¢ Travel to HIGH travel risk states should be for essential purposes and should be\narranged in close liaison with local contacts. Carefully plan all aspects of your itinerary\nand be confident in accommodation, transport, communication and security\narrangements prior to travel. Measures include travelling with a private vehicle and\ntrusted driver and undertaking movement in daylight hours only. Journey plans should\nallow sufficient time for delays, such as a breakdown.\n‚Ä¢ Where possible, avoid all election-related gatherings and polling stations to mitigate the\nrisk of incidental exposure to unrest. Should demonstrators, armed groups or the\nsecurity forces begin to gather, quickly and calmly vacate the area.\n‚Ä¢ Anticipate heightened security and associated disruption during election-related\nevents. Liaise with local contacts for information on planned rallies and allow additional\ntime to reach your destination.\n‚Ä¢ Monitor our alerts on Mexico for further updates.\n', '\nMexico: Avoid political gatherings, exercise vigilance around\nmidterm elections on 6 June\n', '21', '1', '', ' -Notice: Mexico - Avoid political gatherings, exercise vigilance around midterm\nelections on6June\n', NULL),
