(693, 'France', 'Crime Risk', 'internationalsos', '2021-05-11', 'Not Recieved', '\n‚Ä¢ Journeys to most MEDIUM travel risk areas ‚Äì including the capital Riyadh, Dammam\n(Eastern province) and Jeddah (Mecca province) ‚Äì can continue with standard\nprecautions.\n‚Ä¢ Journeys to strategic locations, such as government and military interests, oil facilities\nand airports, in the MEDIUM travel risk areas of Asir, Jizan and Najran provinces within\n68 miles (110km) of the border with Yemen should be for essential purposes only.\nMonitor events closely during your stay in these areas.\n‚Ä¢ Avoid non- essential journeys to the HIGH travel risk areas within 18.6 miles (30km) of\nthe border with Iraq and Yemen. Essential travel to these locations should be\nconducted only with a trusted bilingual local guide, ideally with a strong local contact\nnetwork, and with solid journey- management plans. Defer all travel to Najran city and\nits immediate surroundings due to the heightened threat of indiscriminate cross- border\nstrikes.\n‚Ä¢ Exercise heightened caution around likely targets for Houthi attacks. These include\ngovernment and military interests, energy infrastructure and airports. Remain indoors\nand take cover under or behind a hard surface if an explosion is heard, as falling debris\nfrom a missile or drone interception can pose risks to those in the vicinity.\n‚Ä¢ Monitor our alerts on Saudi Arabia for updates.\n', '\nSaudi Arabia: Asir, Jizan provinces: Fresh cross-border attacks\nhighlight need for caution around potential targets\n', '66', '1', '', ' -Notice: Saudi Arabia -Asir, Jizan provinces: Fresh cross-border attacks highlight\nneed for caution around potential targets\n', NULL),
