(706, 'Benin', 'Crime Risk', 'internationalsos', '2021-05-13', 'Not Recieved', '\nDo the following:\n‚Ä¢ All travellers are recommended to be fully immunised (including a booster if available)\nprior to arrival in country. Carry proof of your polio vaccination status in case it is\nrequested on entry.\n‚Ä¢ Select food, water and other beverages carefully:\no Drink only boiled or bottled water, or sealed carbonated beverages.\no Choose food that has been thoroughly cooked while fresh and is served hot.\no Avoid ice, raw fruit, and raw vegetables (including salad).\n‚Ä¢ Pay attention to hygiene. Wash your hands frequently, especially before eating.\n‚Ä¢ To prevent international spread of polio, the World Health Organization recommends\nthat all residents and visitors who have been in the country for more than 4 weeks\nreceive a dose of polio vaccine (IPV) within 4 weeks to 12 months of travel. Travellers\nshould carry the document on which their polio vaccination status is recorded. They\nmay be asked to show proof of polio vaccination at departure or while entering other\ncountries.\n', '\nBenin: Polio\n', '0', '3', '', ' -Advisory: Benin -Polio\n', NULL),
