(715, 'CentralAfricanRepublic', 'Crime Risk', 'internationalsos', '2021-05-14', 'Not Recieved', '\n‚Ä¢ Avoid all protests as a precaution. Liaise with local contacts for further details of the\nevents and to plan routes bypassing them. If travel in the vicinity of a protest is\nunavoidable, reconfirm the status of routes before setting out and allow additional time\nfor journeys.\n‚Ä¢ Do not attempt to cross any roadblocks erected by demonstrators, as this may prompt\na hostile response. If you come across one, turn around and find another route to your\ndestination.\n‚Ä¢ Leave an area at the first sign of unrest, or if protesters and/or security force personnel\nare gathering. When safe to do so, move to a secure location, such as your\naccommodation or local office, and remain there until the situation stabilises.\n‚Ä¢ Anticipate heightened security around protests and follow all official directives. Comply\nwith internal measures, including movement restrictions linked to COVID-19.\n‚Ä¢ Monitor our alerts on the Central African Republic (CAR) for updates.\n', '\nCentral African Republic: Bangui: Anticipate further protests\nover UN presence, perceived foreign interference\n', '0', '3', '', ' -Advisory: Central African Republic -Bangui: Anticipate further protests over UN\npresence, perceived foreign interference\n', NULL),
(716, 'France', 'Crime Risk', 'internationalsos', '2021-05-07', 'Not Recieved', '\nInbound/outbound business travellers\n‚Ä¢ Defer all travel to Chad due to the current security situation and overarching impact of\nthe COVID-19 pandemic.\n‚Ä¢ For those departing the country, abide by COVID-19 requirements by showing a\nnegative polymerase chain reaction (PCR) test result, taken no more than 72 hours\nprior to departure. Ensure you comply with relevant COVID-19 restrictions at the\nonward destination.\nRemaining essential workforce\n‚Ä¢ All movement should be conducted with a robust risk assessment. Confirm the\nfeasibility of journeys with local contacts or security providers in case of roadblocks en\nroute to your destination.\n‚Ä¢ Prepare to minimise movement on 8 May. Plan all movement around this date\naccordingly.\n‚Ä¢ Non-essential workforce and dependants should defer their return to Chad until at\nleast 10 May.\n‚Ä¢ We do not hold information on specific flights. Only undertake travel to Ndjamena\nInternational Airport (NDJ) upon confirmation of flight schedules. Appropriate check-ins\nshould be made with your relevant manager upon departure and arrival at the facility.\n‚Ä¢ Anticipate a visible military presence and ensure you have valid identification on your\nperson for all related checks. Checkpoints may be erected at short notice. Identify\nalternative routes for all essential movement.\n‚Ä¢ Ensure the ability to stand fast for a minimum of seven days with access to secure\naccommodation, tested, multi-channel and resilient means of communication and\nprocedures, and a robust local assistance network. Ensure access to adequate stocks\nof essential supplies, including food, water, back-up power, fuel, cash and essential\nmedication.\n‚Ä¢ Maintain alternative modes of communication and anticipate potential mobile internet\noutages and spontaneous cuts to mobile telecommunications. Consider purchasing\nmultiple SIM cards, including from neighbouring countries.\n‚Ä¢ Remain apprised of the situation through International SOS alerts and diplomatic and\nsecurity contacts. Do not act upon unverified information.\n', '\nChad: Minimise movement on 8 May during fresh opposition\nprotests; monitor developments in coming days\n', '0', '3', '', ' -Advisory: Chad -Minimise movement on8May during fresh opposition protests;\nmonitor developments in coming days\n', NULL),
