(726, 'France', 'Crime Risk', 'internationalsos', '2021-05-15', 'Not Recieved', '\n‚Ä¢ Monitor the Maldives Meteorological Service website for up- to- date information on\nprevailing weather conditions and related warnings. Be prepared to adjust itineraries\naccordingly.\n‚Ä¢ Liaise with local contacts to ascertain the status of roads before setting out. Do not\nattempt to drive through flooded areas. Turn around and find an alternative route to\nyour destination. Do not self-drive unless very familiar with local conditions.\n‚Ä¢ Avoid walking through submerged areas due to the possibility of uncovered drains,\ndeep ditches and other obstructions that are often unmarked and can prove fatal.\n‚Ä¢ Charge all communication devices and laptops. Ensure you have access to back- up\ncharging options, such as power banks.\n‚Ä¢ Monitor our alerts on the Maldives for updates.\n', '\nMaldives: Exercise caution, plan journeys accounting for\ndisruption caused by ongoing adverse weather\n', '0', '3', '', ' -Advisory: Maldives -Exercise caution, plan journeys accounting fordisruption\ncaused byongoing adverse weather\n', NULL),
(727, 'France', 'Crime Risk', 'internationalsos', '2021-05-10', 'Not Recieved', '\nInbound business travellers\n‚Ä¢ International SOS maintains its standing advice to defer all travel to Myanmar due to\nrestrictions related to COVID- 19. The driver for this advice now applies equally to the\nprevailing security situation, until otherwise indicated. This assessment is made jointly\nby our medical and security professionals.\nIn-country workforce\n‚Ä¢ Essential movement should be carried out after liaising with local contacts to confirm\nthe status of routes and feasibility of travel due to potential roadblocks. Unrest may\noccur with little warning, even in areas that are not traditionally protest hotspots.\nBackup plans should also be in place in the event that the journey is interrupted,\nincluding potential safe havens en route to the destination.\n‚Ä¢ Stand fast in a safe location if in the vicinity of unrest. Should protesters or the security\nforces begin to gather in your vicinity, vacate the area to minimise the risk of injury,\nhead to a safe haven immediately and remain there until the situation has stabilised.\n‚Ä¢ Before conducting any intercity movement or movement outside major urban centres,\nseek a profile- and itinerary- specific risk assessment from security professionals to\nensure appropriate precautions, taking into account the potential for short- notice\nimposition of restrictions on road movement, access to certain areas and\ncommunications services.\n‚Ä¢ Expect heightened security on the streets especially in the capital Naypyitaw,\nMandalay (Mandalay region) and Yangon. C arry relevant identification documents to\nease passage through security checks.\n‚Ä¢ Installations affiliated to the ruling military State Administration Council (SAC), including\nmilitary, police, and local administrative buildings and personnel, are common targets\nof explosions and EAO attacks. Minimise time spent in the vicinity of these locations to\nmitigate the risk of getting caught up in any incident.\n‚Ä¢ Maintain heightened awareness in public spaces, especially in the vicinity of parked\nvehicles or publicly accessible containers such as rubbish bins , due to the threat of\nhidden explosives.\n‚Ä¢ Be prepared for further short- notice disruption to telecommunications services.\nMaintain a list of emergency contacts, both electronically and on paper. Always keep\ncopies with you. Register all contacts on your mobile phone. Ensure that you are aware\nof and compliant with your organisation\'s communications and incident management\nprotocols. Check in or communicate your status and whereabouts during and after any\nperiod of communications disruption.\n‚Ä¢ Power cuts are expected in the coming weeks. Ensure your accommodation has a\nbackup generator and all communication devices are fully charged as a general\nbackup generator and all communication devices are fully charged as a general\nprecaution.\n‚Ä¢ Ensure you have the ability to stand fast for a protracted period with access to secure\naccommodation, tested communications procedures and a resilient local assistance\nnetwork. Ensure access to adequate stocks of essential supplies, including food, water,\nbackup power, fuel, cash and essential medication.\n‚Ä¢ Those travelling near ongoing protests face the risk of arbitrary detention and incidental\ninjury. The police may stop you for questioning, check identification and conduct\nsearches of electronic devices for politically sensitive material.\n‚Ä¢ Continue to monitor developments closely. All information circulating on social media\nand news channels should be verified via reliable sources.\nHealth advice from International SOS\n‚Ä¢ Obtain profile- specific advice prior to any travel, taking into account the extent to which\nyour age and health may make you more vulnerable to the COVID- 19 virus. Review\nthe necessity of travelling against the potential risks.\n‚Ä¢ Do not travel if you are sick. People who are sick risk being tested and quarantined.\nMonitor your health and seek medical attention if you develop flu- like symptoms,\nfollowing the local procedure for your location.\n‚Ä¢ Pay strict attention to hygiene. Wash your hands frequently and carry hand sanitiser for\nuse when soap and water are not readily available. Wear a mask whenever you are\nrequired to. Even if it is not required, consider wearing a mask if you have to go out in\npublic.\n‚Ä¢ Avoidcrowdedplaces.Inpublicareas,asmuchaspossible,keepthree-to-sixfeet(1- 2\nmetres) away from others.\n', '\nMyanmar: Incidental risks remain elevated amid explosions,\nperiodic unrest; conduct essential movement after confirming\nstatus of routes\n', '0', '3', '', ' -Advisory: Myanmar -Incidental risks remain elevated amid explosions, periodic\nunrest; conduct essential movement after confirming status ofroutes\n', NULL),
(728, 'France', 'Crime Risk', 'internationalsos', '2021-05-19', 'Not Recieved', '\n‚Ä¢ Installations affiliated with the ruling military State Administration Council (SAC),\nincluding military, police and local administrative buildings or personnel, are often\ntargeted in bombings. Minimise time spent in the vicinity of these locations as a\nprecaution.\n‚Ä¢ Maintain heightened awareness in public spaces, especially in the vicinity of parked\nvehicles or publicly accessible containers such as rubbish bins, due to the threat of\nhidden explosives.\n‚Ä¢ Expect heightened security near targeted areas. Carry relevant identification\ndocuments to ease passage through security checks and follow all official directives.\n‚Ä¢ Monitor our Myanmar alerts for updates.\n', '\nMyanmar: Yangon: Explosion near UNDP building highlights\nneed for vigilance, incidental risks\n', '0', '3', '', ' -Advisory: Myanmar -Yangon: Explosion near UNDP building highlights need for\nvigilance, incidental risks\n', NULL);
