(858, 'Colombia', 'Crime Risk', 'everbridge', '2021-05-18', ' Bogota, Colombia', '\n‚Ä¢ Avoid affected areas. If you are nearby, minimise movement until the situation\nstabilises.\n‚Ä¢ If planning to travel near an affected area in the coming hours, ensure routes are clear\nprior to setting out.\n‚Ä¢ Monitor our alerts on the Palestinian Territories for updates.\n', ': N/A\n\nmarchas-bogota-en-directo-588829\nThe U.S. Embassy in Bogota reports that the following protests have been planned across\nBogota for Wednesday, May 19:\n8:00 AM local time Demonstration at Portal Americas\n8:00 AM Demonstration at Parque Virrey\n9:00 AM March starting at Parque Nacional; ending point unknown\n10:00 AM March starting at Portal del Sur and proceeding to Estado el Campin\n1:00 PM Demonstration at Parque Banderas\n2:00 PM Demonstration at Monumento a los Heroes\nThe pubic is advised to closely monitor local media outlets, as additional bouts of protest\nactivity could potentially crop up with little or no warning. Widespread protest activity has\ncontinued on a daily basis since late April. What began as a series of demonstrations\nagainst a proposed tax reform initiative has since broadened into a much wider protest\nmovement. Many activists have demanded that the country s riot police force (the Mobile\nAnti-Disturbances Squadron, or ESMAD ) be dismantled following a series of incidents in\nwhich officers have been accused of using excessive force. Student groups, labor unions,\nindigenous organizations, and a range of other activist groups also continue to take to the\nstreets to raise disparate grievances spanning issues such as healthcare, wealth\ninequality, and working conditions.\nProtests have repeatedly degenerated in wider episodes of unrest, sometimes entailing\nlooting, arson, roadblocks, and/or violent clashes with security forces. Dozens of bus\nstops remain out of service throughout Bogota and its environs due to recent vandalism.\nAll large public gatherings should be avoided as much as possible to minimize the risk of\nbeing caught up in incidental violence. Motorists are advised not to attempt to bypass\nroadblocks, as doing so could elicit a violent response from protesters.\n', '0', ' Severe\n', ' N/A', ' VCC Alert -Cundinamarca; Bogota, Colombia Alert: Bogota Protests planned in at least six\ndifferent locations across the city forWednesday, 5/19.\n', NULL),
