(1238, 'China', 'Security Risk', 'everbridge', '2021-06-04', ' Hong Kong, China', '\n‚Ä¢ Avoid affected areas. If you are nearby, minimise movement until the situation\nstabilises.\n‚Ä¢ If planning to travel near an affected area in the coming hours, ensure routes are clear\nprior to setting out.\n‚Ä¢ Monitor our alerts on the Palestinian Territories for updates.\n', ': 0.7 km\n\narrested-june-4-anniversary\nNew Updates:\nMedia sources indicate that thousands of police forces have been deployed to Victoria\nPark from 4:00 PM local time on Friday, June 4, to 12:00 AM on Saturday, June 5, to\nprevent demonstrators from gathering. An annual demonstration has been held at Victoria\nPark in the past on June 4 to commemorate the 1989 Tiananmen Square massacre;\nthousands of protesters of protesters attended the vigil in the past. The vice-chairperson\nof the Hong Kong Alliance in Support of Patriotic Democratic Movements of China, Chow\nHang-tung, was arrested on Friday morning local time for allegedly promoting the banned\nTiananmen vigil. It is not immediately clear if demonstrators will turn out this year due to a\nrecent ban on gatherings. Avoid the area and expect associated disruptions in the vicinity.\nPrevious Updates:\nDemonstrations across Hong Kong initially broke out in June 2019, originally called by the\nCivil Human Rights Front (CHRF), in opposition to a proposed law allowing extraditions to\nmainland China. While the extradition bill was withdrawn, the CHRF and its supporters\nexpanded their demands to include the release of detained protesters, the resignation of\nHong Kong Chief Executive Carrie Lam, an investigation into police responses to the\nprotests, universal suffrage for local elections, and retraction of the use of the word riot to\ndescribe the protests. In 2020, demonstrators have also protested a national security law\nfor Hong Kong passed by the Chinese central government and a ban on insults to the\nChinese national anthem. Some demonstrations in 2019 saw participation levels as high as\nseveral hundred thousand or more than one million; however, the size and frequency of\nprotests have declined this year due to the COVID-19 outbreak and greater government\nrestrictions on the protest movement. Individuals are advised to monitor developments\nand to avoid any demonstrations due to the potential for clashes.\n', '0', ' Severe\n', ' 0.7 km', ' VCC Alert -Wan Chai; Central and Western, Hong Kong (SAR); China Alert: Hong Kong\nThousands ofpolice deployed to Victoria Park onJune 4to prevent Tiananmen Square vigil\n', NULL),
